      "<span><p>In our musical journey to Divyadesams the 26th Divya Desam is Thiruinthalur. From Mayilaaduthurai we have to travel 3 miles towards North and cross the Cauvery river and reach the shrine. The presiding deity is Parimala Renganathar also known as Maruviniya mainthan. Thaayar name is Parimala Renganayaki.</p><p>This is also a shrine of saapa vimochana for Chandran (moon). When Thirumangai aazhwaar came to this shrine since the Pooja was over the temple door was closed. He was upset but still composed paasuram on Parimala Rengan. When the door was not opened he was much disappointed and with frustration he told the Lord to keep His temple with him and sang a paasuram in Tamil what is known as Vasai Vaazhthu Paattu. The Lord showed His grace the door opened and Aazhwaar had the Dharshan.</p><p>The two holy rivers incarnations as two holy women namely Ganga and Cauvery are sitting near the presiding deity to do the service.</p><p>Adiyen composed a Krithi on this Lord and tuned to Ataanaa raagam. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
