    songIntro:
      "<span><p>The 27th Vaishnava Divya desam is Thirukkaavalampaadi located in Thirunaangur of Mayilaaduthurai district. It is one among the 11 Divyadesams of Thirunaangur thiruppathis. One has to reach a shrine called Thiruvellakulam also known as Annan Perumal koil on Sirkaazhi--Tharangampaadi road from  where  one can get the help of Archagar of this temple to have Dharshan of all 11 shrines of Thennaangur Divyadesams.</p><p>The annual festival is the Eleven Garuda Sevai performed on the next day of Amavasai of the Tamil month Thai when all the 11 deities are taken as a procession and assembled in Manimaadakoil Divyadesam. Thirumangai aazhwaar and his wife Kumuthavalli Thaayar will will be worshipping all the 11 Perumals on Garudan one by one and praise the Perumal by paasuram. After that they will get the satari of respective perumaal .Then Manavaalamamuigal will worship Thirumangai aazhwaar Lakhs of people will assemble to see this festival on that day every year.</p><p>Adiyen composed a Krithi on Gopalakrishnan of Thirukkaavalampaadi and tuned to Raagam Dhanyaasiand. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
