      "<span><p>Kazhiseramavinnagaram (a) Sirkaazhi is the 28th Divyadesam is in Mayilaaduthurai district. The temple situated in Sirkaazhi is known as Thaadaalan koil. The presiding deity is Thiruvikramaperumaal. Urchava moorthy is known as Thaadaalan.</p><p>In Tamil Thaal means earth or world Aalan means Ruler. This place was believed to be one where Sage Viswamithra conducted yagna. The place was in ruins for some time while an old lady was believed to have protected the urchava moorthy in a pot of rice bran and worshipped from whom Thirumangai aazhwaar got the idol and reconstructed the temple so as continue the pooja systematically. Hence this God is called Thavittupaanai Thaadaalan.</p><p>By the grace of this Lord Aazhwaar defeated Thiugnana Sambandar in a poetic debate by composing a song Tamil with a count of one two three to seven when Sambandar asked him to construct a small poem called Kural in Tamil. Upon realising Aazhwaar's excellence in Tamil poetic ability Sambandar praised him and gave him his Vel to Aazhwaar.</p><p>I have composed a Krithi on Lord Thaadaalan and tuned to the raagam Madhuvanthi. Madhuvanthi is a raagam Carnatic music borrowed from Hindusthaani music. It was a derived from a raagam known as Dharmavathi. Madhuvanthi literally meaning Honey flowing from flowers. It is a romantic raagam based on foundation eternity and Colors of love. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
