      "<span><p>We will see the 30th Divya Desam Thiruvanpurudothamam through our musical journey which is situated in Thirunaangur near Seerkaazhi.The presiding deity is VanPurudothaman and thaayaar is Purudothamanaayaki. The shrine is one among 11 Thirunaangur Divyadesams involed in 11 Garuda Sevai festival.</p><p>SriRaman from Ayodhya has adorned this shrine as Van Purushothaman. Just like the incident at Seerkaazhi where goddess Parvathi came to feed Thirugnana sambanthar with milk when he was crying near the temple tank in this shrine also an incident was said to have taken place. When Upamanyu the child of Vyakkrapaathar (Pulikkaal munivar) started crying upon not seeing his father who has gone to Nanthavanam leaving him in the temple sannithi Lord VanPurushothaman brought Thirppaarkadal here and Purushothama naayaki fed the child with milk. The holy tank in this shrine is known as Thirppaarkadal Pushkarani or Thiruppaarkadal theertham.Thirumangai aazhwaar praised this Lord in 10 paasurams.</p><p>Adiyen composed a Krithi on this shrine and tuned to raagam Maaya maalava gowlam.  Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
