    songIntro:
      "<span><p>Thirumanimadakoil or Naaraayana Perumal koil is the 32nd Divyadesam and one among the11 Thirunaangur thiruppathis in the outskirts of Seerkaazhi. Presiding deity is Badrinaarayanan and Thaayar name is Pundareeka valli (Thanaraikanni Thaayar).</p><p>As per one legend the sages Madangar, Domyar, Vyaakrapaathar and Udhangar set up their hermirages. According to another legend during the period of the Mahabharata the mighty snake king Thakshakan who actually killed King Parikshith ruled this place. The place was originally called as Naagapuri and eventually became Naangur.</p><p>As per another legend Mahavishnu appeared before Lord Shiva who was performing Rudhra thaandavam because of the demise of his consort Uma in the yanga of Dhaksha. Mahavishnu appeared as Nara-Naraayanan from  Badrinath. All the Devas came to this place to seek the Thirumanthira upadesam from Him. As He spreads the Gnana just like a ever glowing lamp spreads the light always Thirumangai aazhwaar referred Him as Nanthaa vilakku in his paasuram. This shrine is the place where all other 10 Thirunaangur thiruppathi urchavars will come on Garuda vaaganam for the annual festival of Pathinoru Garuda Sevai on the next day of Thai Amavasai.</p><p>Adiyen composed a Krithi on this Naaraayana Perumal and tuned to raagam Shubha pantuvaraali. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
