      "<span><p>திருவெள்ளக்குளம் also known as Annankoil or Annanperumal koil is one among the 11 Thiruppathis of Thirunaangur. The presiding deity is known as AnnanPerumal(Srinivasan). Thaayaar is Alarmel mangai.</p><p>Prince Swethan of Surya vamsam had an indication in his horoscope fora premature death at an age of 9years. To alleviate the fate as per the advise of Saint Vashishtar he came to this shrine and performed thapa by chanting the manthra for long life praying this deity near the pond situated adjacent to the temple. By the grace of this lord he got extended life span. This pond (pushkarani) was named after Swethan as Swetha pushkarani which means vellai kulam in tamil which later turned to Vellakulam.</p><p>Thirumangai Aazhvaar once praised Lord Srinivasan of Thirumalai as Anna(elder bother). After that he had not praised any lord of any Divya Desam. But when he visited this shrine he praised this lord as Anna. Hence this lord was considered elder brother of Lord Balaji of Thirumalai. The speciality of this sthalam is that both Lord Srinivasan and Alarmel mangai are seen in the same sannithi unlike Thirumalai where Thaayaar is in the foot of the hill while Srinivasan is seen at the top of the hill.</p></span>",
