    songThalam: "Roopaka",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>Thirupaarthanpalli is the 39th Divya desam. One can reach this sthalam which is about 12 k.m  from Seerkaazhi. From Thiruvenkadu one has to travel about 2 miles to reach this place. Paadma puraanam had a mention about this sthalam.</p><p>When Arjuna visited this place which was a forest he was very thirsty. He saw Saint Agasthiar wasin thapam. Arjuna requested Agasthiar to provide some water. When Agasthiar looked in to his kamandal he saw that it was dry. By his gnana drishti he realised that this was a trick by Lord Krishna. So he questioned Arjuna that whenever he was facing any problem he used to seek the help of Krishna and why he didn't do this time. Arjuna realised his mistake and prayed to Lord Krishna who appeared before him and gave him a sword (Khatgam in Sanskrit) and asked him to dig the earth. Upon digging the soil Ganges came out as a fountain and became a pond which is known as Khtaga theertham. Just like kurukshetra Lord Krishna made Upadesam to Arjuna in this place also and hence it was originally known as Parthasarathi palli which later on changed as Parthan palli.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on the presiding deity Thaamaraiyal kelvan and Thaayaar Thaamarai naayagi  set to raagam Aabhogi. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
