      "<span><p>In our musical journey to Vaishnava Divyadesams the 40th Divya Desam is Chidhambaram alias Thillainagar. It is also known as Thiruchithrakoodam, situated in the premises of Lord Nataraja temple.</p><p>During the period of Ramayana when Rama was in search of Sita, he came to this place and was impressed by the nature's beauty here. It was as that of Chitrakoot of North India. Hence the name Thiruchithrakoodam.</p><p>The presiding deity is Govindarajan and Thaayaar's name is Pundareekavalli meaning goddess with eyes resembling lotus flowers. In purana it was mentioned that Lord Govindarajan acted as judge to assess the dance competition between Nataraja and Parvathi.</p><p>Kulasekar Aazhvaar praised this lord as kalyana Raman in his paasurams.Thirumangai Aazhvaar praised him in his 32 paasurams seeing his slanting posture as one enchanted by the dance of Lord Nataraja.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on this Divyadesam and tuned the song in the raagam Maand. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
