    songIntro:
      "<span><p>The 44th Divyadesam is Attapuyakaram situated at a distance of about 1mile from  Varadharaja perumal koil of Kancheepuram.</p><p> In puraana it was mentioned that to protect the Yaga of Brahma from  the demon Nakkaran who was sent by Kali, Lord Mahavishnu came with a roopa who had eight arms holding eight weapons. He fought with Nakkayran and killed him simultaneously calmed down the anger of Kali.</p><p>Another incident which had a mention is giving Mukthi to the elephant Gajendran. This incident was again shown by the Lord to Peyaazhwaar when he prayed Him for this.</p><p>When ThirumangaiAazhwaar visited this shrine to worship the Lord, he was stunned to see the posture as he had never ever seen Thirumaal with 8 hands and 8 weapons. So he wrote the paasurams questioning who was He - was He Vishnu or someone else?</p><p>In another incident in Puraana it was mentioned that when big snake entered the temple it got frightened by the posture of the Lord and surrendered to Him. This snake Sarabesan was given protection by the Lord and assigned with the work of taking care of Yaga sala of the temple.</p><p>Adiyen composed a song on this Lord and tuned it to raagam  Keeravani. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy. </p></span>",
