    songIntro:
      "<span><p>Thiruthanka or Thooppul is the 45th Divyadesam located in Kancheepuram.</p><p>The presiding deity is Dheepa prakaasar believed to have appeared in front of Brahma who was performing the Yaga. When it was interfered by an Asura the whole world  became dark. Since Lord Mahavishnu appeared as light Brahma could successfully  complete the Yaga. So Lord Mahavishnu was known in the name of Dheepa prakaasar in Sanskrit while in Tamil with the name Vilakkoli Perumal. Thaayaar name is Maragatha valli.</p><p>Vedhantha Desikan  (1268-1369CE) who was born in this kshethram was an ardent devotee of Dheepa prakaasar temple at Thooppul. Vedhantha Desikan has a shrine in this temple and a separate temple for the statue of Hayagriva worshipped by him also has a temple nearby.</p><p>Adiyen composed a Krithi on Dheepa prakaasar and tuned to Navarasa Kannada raagam. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
