    songRagam: "Vasantha",
    songThalam: "Aadi",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>The next Divya Desam which is 46th in our musical journey is திருவேளுக்கை. Vel meaning wish while Irukkai means seat. Lord Narasimha himself wished to stay here to help his bhakthaas. Hence this place was named as திருவேள்இருக்கை which then changed in due course as Thiruvelkkai.</p><p>The presiding deity is Azhagia singar (Yoga Narasimhar). Thaayaar's name is Velukkaivalli or Amirthavalli.</p><p>Lord Mahavishnu gave dharshan to sage Bruhu in this place. After killing Hiranyan Lord Narasimha chased other Asuras when reached this place was much fascinated by the nature's beauty of this place and hence willing to stay  here itself.</p><p>Among the Aazhvaars, Peyaazhwaar and Thirumangai Aazhwaar praised this shrine in their paasurams. Swami Desikan wrote Kamasikashtakam Kaama+Aashika meaning standing on His own wish.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on this shrine tune to raagam வசந்தா. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
