    songLyrics:
      "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ZS4zuC8GFVtYTXVB6QUSQVotbpfnftYb/preview",
    songTitle: "Kacchi Nagar",
    songURL:
      "https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1438792501&color=%23b4e8e8&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false",
    songRagam: "Kaapi Narayani",
    songThalam: "Aadi",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>The 49th Divyadesam Thiru Nilathingal thundam is situated with in the precincts of Sr Ekambareshwarar temple of Kancheepuram. The shrine is located in the Easanya corner (North East) of the Ekambareshwarar koil prakaram. This is a temple in temple (Vishnu temple inside a Shiva temple). It is the one and only Vaishnava Divyadesam where the poojas are performed by shaivaite priests.</p><p>When Goddess Parvathi had to be born as Kaathyayani due to shapa of Easwaran was brought up by Rishi Kathyayanar. He asked Kathyayani to perform a sincere Penance to reunite with Lord Shiva. So she started doing the penance under a mango tree standing with one leg on a needle unde a mango tree in this place. When Lord Shiva wanted to test her patience he burnt the mango tree with the fire which he released from his third eye on the forehead. Parvathi immediately prayed to her brother Shreeman Narayanan who came to her rescue. With his cool rays as that of a moon he not only brought down the heat on her body but also made the burnt mango tree to regrow which turned back to fully green. By this Parvathi could complete her Penance and got married to Lord Shiva again.</p><p>As Lord Mahavishnu emits cold rays of moon light and broke down the trouble by coming to Parvathi's Penance He was known as Nilathingal Thundathaan.</p><p>Thirumangai Aazhwar praised this shrine in one paasuram. In his Nootriyettu Thiruppathi Anthadhi Saint Pillaiperumal Iyengaar also praised this Lord. Thaayaar's name is Neroruvar illaa valli naachiyaar. It is reported that once there was a separate shrine for this thaayaar in the temple. But now there is no separate sannathi for thaayaar.</p><p>Adiyen composed a Krithi on this deity and tuned to Raagam KAAPI NARAYANI.  Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
