    songTitle: "Thirukaaraga Karunakara",
    songURL:
      "https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1438751362&color=%23b4e8e8&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false",
    songRagam: "Vaachaspathi",
    songThalam: "Aadi",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>In our musical journey to DDs let us visit 52nd Divya Desam Thirukkaaragam. This shrine is situated in the third circle (prakaram) of Ulagalandha perumal koil (Thiruooragam) of Kancheepuram. Thiruooragam temple enshrines three other DDs - Thiruneeragam, Thirukkaaragam and Thirukkaarvaanam and so there are totally 4 Divyadesams in one and the same temple.</p><p>The moolavar is Karunakara perumal in a sitting posture only Aadhiseshan. Thaayaar's name is Padmamani naachiyaar. She is also known by the name Ramamani.</p><p>As per Hindu legend sage Garga performed his penance at this shrine and got the blessings of Karunakara perumal and hence the name Gargaham which later became Kaaragam.</p><p>Adiyen composed a Krithi on Karunakara perumal and tuned to a raagam called VAACHAS PATHI meaning God of Speech. Since Karunakara perumal has a special power of blessing His adiyaars with more knowledge and fame Adiyen selected this raagam for this song. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
