    songIntro:
      "<span><p>We are proceeding to 54th Divyadesam திருக்கள்வனூர் in our musical journey. This is situated just behind the Sanctum sanctorum of Kamatchi Amman temple of Kanchipuram.</p><p>Thirumangai Aazhvaar praised this lord quoting the word 'kalva' in his one paasuram. The presiding deity is Adhi varaha perumal and Thaayaar's name is Anjilaivalli Naachiaar. No separate Urchavar.</p><p>In the puraana it was quoted that once Goddess Lakshmi and Parvathi were chatting when Varaha perumal was hiding himself and hearing their discussion. Knowing that Parvathi called him as Kalvan. When Lord Varaha tried to hide further a demon came out and Parvathi and Lakshmi got frightened. So the lord faught with the demon pushed down and   stood on him. When he tried to jump lord sat on him. Then He pushed the demon down to Paathaala and had lying posture. Parvathi saw all the three postures.</p><p>One achaariar Azhagiya manavala daasan alias Pillaiperumal Iyengar in his Ashta prabhantham (Nootriettu thiruppathi anthathi) praised Lord Adhivaraha perumal.<p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on Lord Varaha of Thirukkalvanur tuned to raagam சிவரஞ்சனி.  Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
