    songThalam: "Deshaadi",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>In our musical journey to Divya Desams we will see the 55th Divya Desam திருப்பவளவண்ணம் (காஞ்சிபுரம்). This shrine is situated in Kaalaandaar street in Kanchipuram.</p><p>Kanchi puranam says that when Lord Brahma proceeded to perform an yaga without accompanying his wife Saraswathi. She got offended and tried to stop the yanga by sending lot of demons. Brahma prayed to Mahavishnu to protect his yanga. Lord Vishnu appeared before him faught with the demons and killed them. As the blood of the demons completely soaked the body of Lord Mahavishnu during the fight his entire body got the color of Coral hence the name பவளவண்ணர் in Tamil.Thaayaar's name is Pavalavalli Thaayaar.</p><p>Thirumangai aazhwaar praised this lord in Thirunedun thaandagam while Azhagiya manavala daasar (Pillaiperumal Iyengar)praised him in Nootriettu thiruppathi anthathi.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on this shrine set to raagam Bahudhari. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
