      "https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1460275753&color=%23b4e8e8&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=fals",
    songRagam: "Nalinakanthi",
    songThalam: "Deshaadi",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>In our musical journey to Divya Desams let us visit 56th Divya Desam திருபரமேச்சுர விண்ணகரம் (வைகுந்தப்பெருமாள் கோவில்) located in Kanchipuram. The temple is considered to be the second oldest one after Kailasanathar temple. The temple was originally built by Pallava king Parameshwara varman (Nandhi varman Pallava mallan ii).</p><p>When the Pallava king vamsam didn't have a child it was said that Lord Mahavishnu himself appeared as a hunter along with Mahalakshmi and gave a child (who was born to sage Bharathwaja and a lady from the heaven) to the then Pallava King. The king named him as Parameswaran. He has been a sincere devotee of Lord Vishnu and constructed this temple. Gracing his prayer Lord Vishnu himself appeared before him and taught him 18 fine arts. As the lord was teaching him the arts He showed the king all his three postures namely standing, sitting and lying. So the Pallava king constructed a three storied temple in which in the ground floor the lord was sculptured in his standing posture and in the first floor in his sitting posture while in second floor in his lying posture.</p><p>Thaayaar's name is Vaikuntha Valli. Thirumangai Aazhvaar who was the contemporary of this Pallava king praised this Paramapatha naadhan in 10 paasurams.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on this shrine tuned to a raagam நளினகாந்தி. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
