    songURL:
      "https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1476752368&color=%23b4e8e8&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false",
    songRagam: "Kalyana Vasantham",
    songThalam: "Roopaka",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>We now continue our musical journey to 57th Divya Desam திருப்புட்குழி. This is situated near a place called Baluchetti chathiram which is about 7 miles of west of Kanchipuram. From that place one has to travel about 2 furlong in southern direction to reach this shrine.</p><p>The purana for this sthalam is similar to that of PullamBoothankudi. In both the places it was said that Lord Rama performed the final rituals for Jadaayu who came to rescue Sita while she was taken by Ravana in pushpaka Vimanam to Srilanka. At the time of performing rituals Rama kept the body of Jadaayu on his right lap. Due to the smell of the burning body of Jadaayu Sridevi usually on the right side Vishnu (born as Rama) moved to his left side.</p><p>Rama by sending an arrow brought a holy water as a pond to perform the final rituals. This pond is named as Jadaayu pushkarani. The temple authorities are of the opinion that the final rituals of Jadaayu performed by Lord Rama at Pullam Boothankudi was reenacted based on the request of Jadaayu put forth to Lord Narayana at Vaikuntam. He made the submission to Narayanan to give the same dharshan to all devotees coming to this shrine. The Thaayaar's name is Maragathavalli.</p><p>Women who are not blessed with child are asked to take bath in the Jadaayu pushkarani along with their respective husband. The priest of this temple hand over a small quantity of roasted pulses or other grains. Those women are asked to have these roasted grains after soaking in water and tying in their sarees. They have to sleep near the sannidhi of Thaayaar along with the grains in their sarees.The next day morning the grains will be examined. If these roasted grains start germinating they are sure to get the blessings of Thaayaar for pregnancy and healthy child. Hence the Thaayaar has a name 'வறுத்த பயறு முளைவித்த தாயார்'. This shrine has another importance. Aachariyar Ramanujarhad his early lessons of Vedhas here only in the gurukula of Yaadhava prakaasar.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on this shrine tuned to a raagam கல்யாண வசந்தம். Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
