      "https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1671545934&color=%23b4e8e8&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false",
    songRagam: "Kanada",
    songThalam: "Deshaadi",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>The next Divya Desam in our musical journey is திருவள்ளூர (திருஎவ்வுள்) which is 59th Divya Desam among the 108 shrines. Presently it is a suburb of Chennai on the road route to Thiruppathi. The shrine was quoted in Markandeya purana.</p><p>During Krutha Yuga Burupunniya and his wife performed an yaga called Sali yanga at Badri seeking blessings of Lord Narayana for a child.Lord Narayanan blessed them and asked them to name their son Salihothran. When Salihothran became an adult he took up an yathra to different shines and holy places. He reached a forest here and saw a pond where Devas used to come and take a holy dip in it. He constructed a hut with a parnashala and performed Pooja regularly. Everyday he used to feed a guest and then only had his food. One day he had wait for a long time for the arrival of a guest. Lord Narayana came in a disguise as an old man for his house as a guest on that day. Salihothra was very happy to receive him and offered food. After taking food the old man told him that he was very tired and wanted to lie down and sleep. He asked Salihithra where was the room to sleep (எவ்வுள்). Saint Salihothra showed a small place near his parnashala and told this was the place to sleep (இவ்வுள்). When the guest in the disguise of an old man lied down he showed that he was Lord Narayana. Saint Salihothra was very happy to the lord in front of him when Lord Narayana asked him his wish. He immediately requested that Lord may please remain there permanently in that posture and bless all bhakthaas. Lord Narayana accepted and blessed him with his hand on the head of Salihothra.</p><p>Moolavar Veeraragava perumal is also known as எவ்வுள் கிடந்தான் Thaayaar's name is கனகவல்லி (வஸுமதி). The holy theertham (pond) in this shrine was supposed to destroy the sins of the devotees. Lord Shiva (Rudra) was also said to have been relieved of his sins he got by killing  Dhaksha when he came here took bath and prayed Lord Veeraragava perumal. By taking bath in the theertham of this shrine and praying Lord, the diseases one experience get cured and hence he is called வைத்திய வீரராகவ பெருமாள்.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on this lord tuned to raagam கானடா. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
