      "https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1671546447&color=%23b4e8e8&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false",
    songRagam: "Karnaranjani",
    songThalam: "Misra Chaapu",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>We will now go to Thiruneermalai through our musical journey which is the 61st Divya Desam found in Chennai near Thambaram which is one among the Thondai nattu thiruppathis. Here Lord Mahavishnu is seen in 4 postures - Nindra (standing), Neer vannan Iruntha (Sitting), Santha Narasimhan Kidantha (lying) as Renganathan and Nadantha (walking) as Thirivikraman. Since the water surrounds the hill during heavy rains this hill was known as Neer malai.</p><p>Once  Rishi Valmiki camehere and worshipped Renga Nathan Narasimhan and Thirivikraman. When he came down the hill he had a little dissatisfaction as he was fond of witnessing Lord Mahavishnu in the roopa of Rama. So he prayed for the dharshan of Rama. To satisfy his prayers Lord Renganatha came in the roopa of Rama while Lakshmi as Sita, Aadhiseshan as Lakshmana, Shang as Bharatha, Chakkara as Chathrukina, Vishwaksenar as Sugreeva and Garudan as Hanuman. Valmiki prayed to show the Neervannan roopa (Rama) to all bakthas who visit this temple which the lord accepted.</p><p>Once Thirumangai aazhwaar came here for dharshan when there was were heavy rains. The entire hill was surrounded by water for a period of six months. He waited in the nearby village till the rains stopped and the water drained completely. He reached the temple and worshipped the lord by composing 19 paasurams. The place where Thirumangai aazhwaar stayed is now known as Thirumangai aazhwaar puram. Bhudhathaazhwar praised this lord in one paasuram. The presiding deity in the foothill is Neervannan and Thaayaar's name is Animaamalar mangai in addition to three other deities on the hill mentioned earlier.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on this Divya Desam and tuned in a raagam known as KARNA RANJANI. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
