      "https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1671547956&color=%23b4e8e8&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false",
    songRagam: "Jayanthashri",
    songThalam: "Deshaadi",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>We are now proceeding to 63rd Divya Desam திருக்கடல்மல்லை(மாமல்லபுரம்). It is near Chennai and lot of buses are plying from Chennai City. Most of the temples and carved temples were constructed by Pallava kings. This is the birth place of Bhoothathaazhvar.</p><p>In Bhagavatha purana one saint Pundareeka maharishi with lotus flowers in a  basket was trying to worship lying posture of Thirumal in Thiruppaarkadal. When he was interrupted by the ocean he tried to clear the water of ocean. Upon seeing his bhakthi Lord Mahavishnu appeared before him in disguise as an elderly person and asked for food, the rishi handed over the flower basket to him asked him to wait near the sea shore so that he could go back to his hut and bring food. Meanwhile Mahavishnu took his original form adorned himself with the flowers tied by Rishi and had a sleeping posture on Aadhiseshan as in Thiruppaarkadal on the sea shore. When the rishi returned he understood the elderly person he met was none other than Mahavishnu. The rishi was so happy and prayed the lord to bless him by permitting him to sit near His holy feet and lord permitted. Since the Lord laid himself on Aadhiseshan in the ground of sea shore without any throne he was designated as தலசயனப் பெருமாள். Bhoothathaazhvar and Thirumangai aazhwaar praised this lord in their paasurams.</p><p>Thaayaar's name is நிலமங்கைத் தாயார். Urchavar holds a lotus flower in his hand in a standing posture and known by the name உலகுய்ய நின்றான்.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on this shrine tuned to a raga known as 'Jeyantha shree'. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.</p></span>",
