      "https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1671548391&color=%23b4e8e8&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false",
    songRagam: "Valaji",
    songThalam: "Aadi",
    songIntro:
      "<span><p>In our musical journey to Vaishnava DDs let us now proceed to 64th Divya Desam திருக்கடிகை (அ) கடிகாசலம்  popularly known as சோளிங்கர் historically called சோழவளசிம்மபுரம் which later on changed as சோளசிம்மபுரம். It is about 25 km from Arakonam RS.</p><p>This sthalam had a mention in Vishnu puranam where it was indicated that sage Viswamithra came to this hill and performed thapa to see Lord Narasimha. When he had the strong prayer for a period of one கடிகை or நாழிகை viz., 24 minutes Lord Narasimha appeared before him.</p><p>Similarly during the end of Thredhayuga Saptharishis when performed thapa to see Lord they were disturbed by two demons Kaalan and Keyan. At that period when Lord Rama was preparing to proceed to Vaikuntam Hanuman wanted to accompany him. Rama told Hanuman to go to this hill and fight with the demons to protect the rishis. When Hanuman had a long fight with the demons he became very tired. He prayed Rama for a solution when Rama appeared and gave him Shank and Chakra with those help Hanuman killed them and saved the thapa of rishis. Praising their sustained efforts Mahavishnu appeared as Lord Narasimha which Hanuman also saw and praised Narasimha through Bajan. Lord Narasimha asked Hanuman to stay there in yoga posture similar to him till the end of Kaliyuga. One can see Hanuman in the neighbouring hill in yoga posture with shank and chakra on the shoulders.</p><p>It is believed that if a person stays in this sthalam and prays for a time of one கடிகை or நாழிகை (24 minutes) he or she will be blessed with Mukthi or Moksham. அசலம் means hill hence the name கடிகாசலம். The presiding deity is Yoga Narasimhar and he is praised as Akkaara kani by Thirumangai aazhwaar in his paasuram. Peyaazhwaar also praised this shrine in his paasuram. Thaayaar's name is அமிர்த வல்லித் தாயார். Urchavar name is Bhakthavathsala perumal.</p><p>Adiyen composed a krithi on this shrine tuned to raagam Valaji. Singers are Dr.Thatham and Mrs.Amutha. Please listen and enjoy.<p></span>",
